Interface ICommand

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Add_money, Pay_off_debt_with_balance, Pay_off_debt_with_savings, Spend_money, Transfer_to_savings

    public interface ICommand
    Commands that can be executed by the Account class
    Author:
    Daniele Palazzo

    • Method Detail

      • doit

        void doit()
   throws Invalid_amount_exception,
          Insufficient_funds_exception,
          No_debt_exception
        Execute the command
        Throws:
        Invalid_amount_exception - A wallet exception that is thrown when calling a Wallet method with an amount that is not valid (e.g. negative value)
        Insufficient_funds_exception - A wallet exception that is thrown when the Wallet does not have enough funds to perform a requested action
        No_debt_exception - A wallet exception that is thrown when attempting to pay off non existent debt in the Wallet

      • undoit

        void undoit()
        Do the opposite of what the doit method does. Undo the command.

      • description

        java.lang.String description()
        The description of the command
        Returns:
        Return a string describing what the command does. (Useful for printing the command history.)

      • get_amount

        double get_amount()
        Returns:
        Return the amount stored in the command. (Useful for printing the command history.)
